Job Description: The Association of Statutory Health Insurance Dentists in Bavaria (KZVB) is looking for a full-time or part-time person to join the legal department as soon as possible  Fully qualified lawyers (m/f/d) Healthcare is a growth industry. Statutory health insurance alone spends over 200 billion euros a year on patient care. The KZVB ensures dental care in Bavaria, bills the health insurance companies for the services provided by Bavarian dentists and supports the practices in implementing legal requirements. It sees itself as a modern service company. As a corporation under public law, the KZVB also represents the interests of contract dentists vis-à-vis politicians and health insurance companies.
We offer you professional development opportunities in a varied and responsible area of ​​responsibility. The remuneration corresponds to the requirement profile: . There are also extensive social benefits including an attractive company pension scheme. You will work in a dedicated, collegial team characterized by great collegiality. You have a future-proof and modern workplace in the Munich district of Mittersendling with a direct S-Bahn connection and you can use the in-house canteen. With your work, you make an active contribution to ensuring that everyone in Bavaria has access to high-quality dental care close to where they live. Applicants (m/f/d) with a severe disability will be given preference if they are equally qualified.  Have we piqued your interest? Then welcome to our team!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: health care, legal representation

Job Description: Specialist consultant (m/f/d) - financial sales
Are you starting out in sales and always getting the best out of your customers? Would you like a job with good pay, appreciation of your work and great colleagues? Then we have something for you: For direct placement to a customer, we are looking for a specialist consultant (m/f/d) for financial sales as soon as possible. Where? You can easily do your job from the home office or directly in the office, which is located in the Pegnitz area.  Apply now
What you bring with you: * You live sales and communication, appear confident in dealing with customers * You have successfully completed your training as an insurance clerk (m/f/d) or bank clerk (m/f/d), for example. Alternatively, you have commercial training or professional experience in sales. * Knowledge of the financial and wealth sector desirable * However, career changers from other sales areas are also very welcome at our customer due to the extensive development opportunities
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Order acceptance and processing
Advanced knowledge: Acquisition, customer advice and support, sales, field service

Job Description: Your tasks  You take care of the maintenance and administration of the IT audit list You regularly check and optimize implemented IT measures You are responsible for communication and coordination with the internal IT teams and across departments They ensure a smooth flow of information between the partners involved within the various IT teams  Your skills Completed commercial training or comparable qualification Confident handling of common Microsoft Office products (e.g. Excel) Independent way of working, as well as planning and organizational skills Initial experience in IT and a basic technical understanding are desirable High communication skills, teamwork and independent work We offer  With us you are not just wasting your time. Instead, we offer you a meaningful job and a career with real prospects! You will receive a fair salary and attractive additional benefits as a bonus. This also includes subsidies for childcare or company pension schemes. As an employee, you can enjoy attractive discounts. You will receive a 20% employee discount on your purchases in the Denns organic markets and you can use the monthly offers on our corporate benefits platform. We also offer you the option of leasing a company bike. Our annual working time account and the possibility of mobile working ensure a flexible organization of your working day. On our own eLearning platform "Wissen macht BIO" you can continue your education with a variety of courses or you can take advantage of our exciting range of further education options. We are looking for team players! That's why our annual team events don't miss out. Our company canteen at the Töpen site takes care of your physical well-being with discounted delicacies and a 100% organic kitchen.

Job Description: - Europes fastest growing board portal solution|This role will be a position in Germany to meet the demand for iBabs  company profile Europe's fastest growing board portal for 2,000+ organisations, iBabs empowers customers to quickly organize effective meetings and make good decisions confidently. Our software application is the best on the market to electronically distribute documents for Board and Committee meetings in a secure manner. We understand the work that goes into meetings - and how to streamline everything so it all flows smoothly on any device - confidentially, securely and automatically.  iBabs is present in Amsterdam, Brussels, London and Paris with every day over 200,000 users securely accessing their meeting documents and attending meetings - anytime, anywhere and on any device.  With our HQ in the Netherlands we have 20 years' experience of delivering meeting solutions. We have a wide variety of customers from PLCs, private companies, Banks, Insurers and Investment funds to charities, housing associations, NHS, State bodies, Councils and Government Ministries. With parent company Euronext we are currently expanding into Norway, Sweden, Finland, Denmark, Portugal, Spain, Germany and Italy. This role will be a position in Germany to meet the demand for iBabs in this market.  area of ​​responsibility As our trainer you are responsible for the successful onboarding and support of our board portal solution for our German-speaking clients within a broad range of organisations, from municipalities to ministries, from small healthcare organizations to large hospitals and from small businesses to large corporates. You will provide training sessions as part of the onboarding process for administrators/secretaries as well as to end-users. These training sessions may be in person or via video conference.  Administrators/secretaries receive a group three hour session so they are able to fully manage their iBabs site. End users who are usually board members and/or executive teams receive a one hour session. Within these sessions you may have those who are IT literate and only need five minutes support to get started right through to Independent board members who may be using technology for the first time. Every company is different as is every training session so you need to be adaptable with great communication skills (both face-to-face and online) However the reward is always the same, customers 'love' iBabs and become evangelical, often recommending us to other companies.  After the onboarding, you are the first point of contact for these clients. You will provide assistance and support for incoming queries and issues related to our board portal solution and any other related duties to support our German-speaking clients. To assist you we have second and third line support desks.  You may also be asked to train and support companies who are having a trial of iBabs. These require shortened training sessions but more hand-holding with weekly calls to ensure their trial is a success and they move to becoming a part of the iBabs family. In addition to the tasks described above, you will support the team in the English speaking market.
requirement profile: -Fluency in German and English is a must, professional capacity in another language is a plus -Excellent training skills and experience - Strong didactic and communication skills -Excellent technical knowledge and ability to interpret technical language for non-technical people - Strong customer support skills - Ability to troubleshoot and diagnose problems - Ability to communicate effectively -Writing and editing skills (to aid in writing and updating manuals) are a plus - Able to work in an autonomous and organized manner -The capacity to work well on your own or in a team Compensation Package  -To be part of a fast-growing and profitable company -To be part of an international and ambitious team - Competitive salary

Job Description: Temporary work convinces! PS Personalservice GmbH has been offering individual solutions with strategy for over 25 years. Your new job is just a mouse click away or a phone call to PS!  For one of our customers based in Kupferzell Criesbach, we are looking for machine and plant operators (m/f/d) for immediate employment. Machine and plant operator (m/f/d)
About us, PS Personalservice GmbH: PS Personalservice GmbH has been offering temporary work out of conviction for over 25 years! In our branch we take care of your concerns and your prospects. We offer you free further training as well as preventive and compulsory examinations. As a long-standing personnel service provider in the Hohenlohe district, we are strongly networked in the job market and therefore have well-known contacts to companies in which you can work. Regardless of whether you are looking for a job in the short, medium or long term, we offer you individual ""solutions with strategy"". Take your chance and become part of our team.  For security reasons, please send us your application documents in PDF format.  Our opening hours are from Monday to Friday 08.00 - 17.00. You can reach us by telephone on 07941 91890.  We look forward to you!  PS Personalservice GmbH Untere Torstrasse 13 74613 Öhringen 07941 9189-0 oehringen@psstrategie.de Machine and plant operator (m/f/d)

Job Description: Lawyer (m/f/d) The German Children's Cancer Foundation is looking for a lawyer (m/f/d) for its office in Bonn as soon as possible. * Coordination of service providers in the areas of foundation law, inheritance law, Data protection, labor law, etc. and its operational implementation in day-to-day business * Advising employees and committees on legal issues * Provision of information about innovations in the legally relevant areas * Further development of your own work area in coordination with the management We offer you * An employment relationship with up to 30 hours per week in a future-proof organization * A meaningful job in a friendly and committed team * Subsidized job ticket * Flexible working hours, mobile working and work-life balance  we expect from you * (Fach) university education in the legal field * Several years of professional experience, ideally in a similar position * Structured and careful way of working, ability to work in a team, resilience and loyalty * Identification with our foundation's purpose of getting involved with children with cancer and their families The German Children's Cancer Foundation promotes and finances clinical and patient-oriented research projects, supports affected families with competent advice and information as well as financial aid in emergencies and operates rehabilitation and leisure facilities on Sylt and in Heidelberg.

Job Description: Industrial mechanic (m/f/d) assembly job code  The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering. We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. Become part of a healthy, 100-year-old family business in mechanical and plant engineering! Your tasks  - You assemble mechanical components including functional testing - You put together parts using bills of materials and pay attention to completeness - Confidently and independently you assemble assemblies according to drawings and later machines and systems - Through the targeted use of measuring and testing equipment, you ensure the perfect quality of our products - Analyze errors and glitches  your qualifications - Successfully completed training as an industrial mechanic (m/f/d), mechatronics technician (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification. - First professional experience in pre-assembly and final assembly in mechanical engineering. - You are a team player and passionate about mechanics. - You are flexible and work project-related if necessary in a 2-shift system. We offer  - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

Job Description: Electrician (m/f/d) installation and control cabinet construction  Job code BEBA-853-8534 The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering. We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. Become part of a healthy, 100-year-old family business in mechanical and plant engineering! Your tasks  - In a team of 20 colleagues you are responsible for the construction, installation, wiring and commissioning of control cabinets - You will install and lay cables on complex machines - You carry out VDE tests - You travel to the customer for commissioning - Analyzing malfunctions and errors your qualifications  - Successfully completed training as an electrician (m/f/d), electronics technician (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - Ideally, first experience in control cabinet construction and machine installation - You are a team player and enthusiastic about electrical engineering. - You are flexible and like to travel We offer - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

Job Description: Plant mechanic (m/f/d) Tank and container builder  Job code BEBA-853-8535 The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources.  Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering.  We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities. Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. The team looks forward to your application!  Your tasks - You manufacture assemblies according to design drawings - You set up systems and attach welding bevels - Tacking, welding, straightening and testing of demanding assemblies - You check parts for distortion and assemble them into complete constructions - They document test results and apply test marks your qualifications  - Successfully completed training as a plant mechanic (m/f/d) specializing in welding technology or a comparable qualification - First professional experience in special machine construction - Skilled craftsmanship

Job Description: Plant mechanic (m/f/d) laboratory assembly  Job code BEBA-853-8536  The KMS Group is a service company in the field of human resources. Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering.  We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities. Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. The team looks forward to your application!  Your tasks - Through careful assembly and installation of our laboratory products at the customer, you will ensure optimal results - They complete and connect the piping system and connect the media piping to the on-site transfer points - You check the piping systems for function and tightness, create the associated protocol and carry out the quality inspection - With your communicative nature, you skillfully conduct coordination and coordination talks with other companies and hand over the sanitary facility, including user instructions, to the customer your qualifications - You have completed training as a plant mechanic (m/f/d) SHK or a comparable qualification - You have manual skills and technical understanding and also want to familiarize yourself with topics such as electronics and everything to do with laboratory furniture - Smooth communication within the team and with customers is good manners for you - You convince with an independent and result-oriented way of working - You have a driver's license and look forward to exciting assembly work (Monday to Friday). We offer  - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering.  We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our customer has its headquarters in Wangen im Allgäu, which operates in Europe and worldwide with a total of around 1,600 employees. Through the development and production of filling systems and process systems, our client manufactures the customer-specific requirements. The team looks forward to your application!  Your tasks  - You operate the woodworking machines with confidence and thus ensure optimal conditions for the downstream production steps - You carry out regular checks of dimensions, drilling and milling patterns. - In the event of deviations, keep a cool head and carry out the necessary parameter adjustments or tool changes at an early stage - The CNC controlled woodworking machine, reprogram if necessary  your qualifications - You have completed training as a carpenter (m/f/d), carpenter (m/f/d), wood mechanic (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - You enjoy the wood product and would like to work in 2 shifts - You are characterized by manual dexterity and spatial imagination - Ideally, you already have professional experience in the operation and maintenance of woodworking machines We offer  - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

Our portfolio includes employee leasing, personnel placement, outsourcing and on-site management in the fields of aviation, vehicle construction, mechanical engineering, steel construction, warehousing / logistics, finance / office and engineering. We offer you an innovative and challenging job, an attractive salary and good development opportunities.  Our international customer is the pioneer in the construction of highly innovative production and automation systems in the region and worldwide! For the team at the Mindelheim location, we are looking for an inquisitive and attentive colleague (m/f/d) with immediate effect. Your tasks  - You take over the creation of mechanical drawing documentation of our plants according to the diverse requirements of our various customers - You prepare both the data formats of the 2D and 3D drawings as well as the master and parts list data from our SAP system according to customer specifications - You are responsible for the creation of customer-specific parts lists and various project lists according to the specifications - You participate in the constant improvement process to automate the recurring processes your qualifications  - Completed vocational training as a technical product designer, in a technical profession, each with a fable for IT solutions - Good MS Office skills - English knowledge in spoken and written - You are characterized by an independent, structured and conscientious way of working - You have the ability to work in a team and willingness to learn - Basic knowledge of AutoCAD and Siemens NX or comparable CAD systems - Basic knowledge of SAP desirable We offer - We help with your personal development! - No boredom! - Challenging tasks, interesting environment - Expiry Date? - Permanent employment

Job Description: We have a job for you! Are you looking for a new professional challenge? Then come to us in Bremen! Here you can fully develop. Take your future as a warehouse logistics specialist into your own hands. One of our customer companies in the food industry is looking for staff as soon as possible as part of temporary employment. Warehouse logistics specialist in Bremen (m/f/d) - You are responsible for acceptance and loading - You operate and monitor the systems - You carry out cleaning and maintenance tasks and create the necessary documentation - You have completed training as a warehouse logistics specialist - You can work both independently and in a team - You have a high sense of quality and responsibility - You have a valid industrial truck license (desirable) - Secure job through a permanent employment contract. - Remuneration according to industry surcharge tariff (TV BZ HK) - Payment of social benefits such as B. Holiday and Christmas bonuses - The chance of being taken on with professional and personal suitability - The MPS team will look after you throughout your employment. - Life means acting, apply now.   The fastest way to your new job is via the blue ""Apply now"" button! The MPS team stands for diversity and equal opportunities, Of course, we welcome applications from people with disabilities. After your application has been received, your dispatcher will contact you promptly. Your MPS team looks forward to seeing you!

Job Description: The state of Berlin is the largest employer in the region. Around 130,000 employees in the immediate state administration work every day to ensure that Berlin functions as a vibrant metropolis and as a home for around 3.65 million people. The staff of the general non-technical administrative service form the backbone of the Berlin administration.  The Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family is responsible for ensuring that all Berliners have good educational opportunities - from early childhood education in daycare to a good school-leaving certificate for vocational training or university studies. It creates the framework for young people and families to feel at home in this city and guarantees support and encouragement in all walks of life. In addition to the approximately 42,000 employees at the Berlin schools, more than 2,000 employees work in the specialist departments of the ministerial part of the Senate Administration for fundamental and operational tasks.   To strengthen its team, Department V - Family and Early Childhood Education - of the Senate Department for Education, Youth and Family is looking for staff (several positions) for the area of ​​responsibility from February 1st, 2023 Clerk in the area of ​​data warehouse - integrated software Berlin youth welfare (DWH-ISBJ) including statistics in the working group statistics and data management (m/f/d)  Code number 29/23  unlimited,
• For the complete job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button ""further information"" (at the bottom of the advertisement). We offer you • an interesting, varied and challenging job in which you can help shape important areas of life in the city of Berlin. • the opportunity to further develop your personal skills by taking advantage of our wide range of technical and non-technical further education and training opportunities and thus opening up career opportunities for yourself.   • An attractive payment, which is based on the TV-L for employees who are not covered by a collective agreement or on the AT payment guidelines of the State of Berlin for employees who are not covered by a collective agreement, and on the Berlin State Salary Act for civil servants. • an additional old-age provision via the VBL (Federal and State Pension Fund).   • the compatibility of career and family through flexible working hours and the possibility of part-time employment within the framework of official needs. If necessary, you can use a parent-child room or, depending on the available places, a place in a nearby day-care center can be arranged. We are certified by the berufundfamilie audit as a family-friendly employer. • A company health management whose offers (e.g. diverse sporting activities) are intended to maintain your health. • good accessibility of your workplace by public transport, for which we can provide you with a BVG job ticket.   • a collegial working atmosphere in a diverse, tolerant and cosmopolitan administration, in which we are committed to equal opportunities. Severely handicapped people and people of equal status will be given preferential treatment if they have the same qualifications. Please indicate in your application if you have a severe disability. Applications from people with a migration background who meet the hiring requirements are expressly encouraged.
Can you find yourself in the profile? Then we look forward to receiving your application by March 20th, 2023 using the “apply now” button below. For the complete job requirements, please refer to the requirement profile: under the button ""further information"" (at the bottom of the advertisement).  Please enclose a CV in tabular form with your application ...

Job Description: Become a postman for letters in Hattingen what we offer * €14.34 standard hourly wage – plus holiday and Christmas bonuses * You can start immediately full-time for a limited period of time, 38.50 hours/week * A crisis-proof workplace, guaranteed salary increase according to the collective agreement and punctual salary payments * Possibility of overtime payment * Free provision of quality workwear * Detailed instruction (paid) - we will get you ready for the delivery * Permanent takeover and development opportunities (e.g. site manager) possible with good performance and open positions * Attractive employee offers such as employer-financed company pension schemes, bicycle leasing, discounts from mobile phone providers, etc. Your duties as a postman for letters * Delivery of letters in 5 working days * Accept and sort mail items * Delivery by bike or on foot What you offer as a deliverer * You can converse in German * You ride your bike safely in traffic * You are weatherproof and can tackle things well * You are reliable and stick to it  Become a postman at Deutsche Post DHL  As a mail carrier, you make the people in your district happy every day and deliver the mail to them. You walk or cycle five working days a week (between Monday and Saturday) and don't let the weather spoil your mood. We also welcome career changers or students, because you count as you are! We look forward to receiving your application as a deliverer, preferably online! Simply click on the 'Apply' button – even without a CV.  CONNECTING PEOPLE, IMPROVING LIVES #becomeoneofus #become one of us mailman #postmanforletters

Job Description: ISZ GmbH operates the CAFM control center of the FHH. This supports the authorities, districts, state companies and city-owned companies in the introduction and regular operation of CAFM and in this context also looks after their own CAFM systems. -  Configuration and maintenance of the IT systems of the CAFM control center and integration into the general IT architecture  - Configuration and parameterization of the CAFM system speedikon C in cooperation with the manufacturer  - Development and creation of customer-specific reports and configurations in the CAFM system  -  Developments, further developments and acceptance of the software with the software manufacturer as well as implementation of tests and documentation/quality assurance -  General support as well as assistance with fault analysis and technical troubleshooting -  Support of the CAFM control center with tasks in the wider IT environment  - Support in the operation of the associated infrastructures in the area of ​​responsibility  - Communication with or control of IT service providers in the area of ​​responsibility  -  Support in ensuring and further developing general IT operations, IT processes and IT security together with external IT service providers -  Advice and support in the development, implementation and further development of interfaces to third-party systems and mobile / web-based applications -  Management and participation of/in internal IT projects  - Responsibilities for data protection and data security of the company  - Experience in the administration, installation and configuration of client and server hardware and software as well as network components  -  Experience in the planning, administration and further development of IT infrastructure, networks and security issues -  Knowledge of the Microsoft environment (Windows Server 2012 - 2019, MS SQL) -

Job Description: As a communication point between tenants and landlords, the ISZ service area MVM-Consulting (MVM = tenant-landlord-model) advises the tenants in a team and in an interdisciplinary manner throughout the entire (structural) development process from service phase 1 as part of the registration and analysis of requirements, e.g. Profitability analyses, interface definitions, plausibility checks of life cycle costs or specific acceptances until the property is moved in and used.  Our ISZ service area is the communication point between tenants and landlords. We are experts in MVM (tenant-landlord-model) consulting. As a project manager, you will advise the tenants on the entire (structural) development process, both in a team and on an interdisciplinary basis. You accompany our tenants from service phase 1, as part of the registration and analysis of requirements, in rental contract negotiations, profitability analyses, interface definitions, the plausibility check of life cycle costs or with specific acceptances up to moving in and using the property. - You will be involved in the neutral advice of the tenant project as well as in the determination of needs and quality assurance of external needs analyses. - In addition, you accompany the users and users in tenant-landlord projects through almost all service phases and in the structure and design of tenant projects. - You take over the initial check and documentation of requirement notifications as well as the inclusion in the requirement register and the regular reporting on requirement notifications. - You are an accompanist in checking the coverage of needs for inventory, rental and purchase. - With your eye for detail, you check the plausibility of rental cost calculations by landlords. - The (formal) consultation and examination of the LOI, as well as the examination of the rent, compliance with standards or deviations, the past project steps, WU and NWA are also part of your area of ​​responsibility. - You take over the accompaniment when handing over the rental property i.Z.m. ABH (defects, unfulfilled requirements, etc.) and the plausibility check of the contractually agreed cost items.  Must have - You have a university degree (bachelor's degree or equivalent) in the field of civil engineering, architecture, real estate management, a comparable field or skills and experience equivalent to these university degrees. - In addition, you have already gained several years of professional experience related to the advertised position. - You have a strong customer orientation as well as very good communication skills and negotiation skills in dealing with stakeholders. - You are assertive and have an independent, analytical and creative approach. - You love to constantly improve internal and external processes. - If you also have a strong team spirit and enjoy working with interdisciplinary teams, then we should get to know each other.  Nice to have  - Many years of practical experience in the planning, control and implementation of building construction measures would be desirable. - Ideally, you have acquired additional qualifications and certificates in project management (IPMA or similar). - You have good knowledge of construction contract law and public procurement as well as municipal real estate management (tenant-landlord model). - Basic business knowledge is also an advantage.  - Work-life balance With us you get flextime, 30 days...

New rental of objects  - On the basis of needs analyses, you determine the need for new rental properties. - You are in charge of finding, examining and selecting locations and buildings considering any urban options. - You carry out contract negotiations on object designs and conditions and conclude rental agreements. - You create benefit analyzes and decision templates.  inventory management - You are responsible for compliance with and changes to existing contracts. - You identify area and cost optimizations in the managed portfolio. - You advise our customers and keep an eye on our scheduled resubmissions. - You are responsible for tracking defects in our existing properties. - You are also responsible for terminating leases and negotiating and terminating contracts.  - You have completed a (technical) university degree in the field of real estate management or have completed training as a real estate clerk and further training as a real estate specialist or a comparable qualification. - You have already gained sound professional experience in a comparable area. - You have very good knowledge of the market. - The secure application of the legal basis in commercial tenancy law is a matter of course for you. - You have experience working with SAP or other rental management systems. - Your appearance is confident in every situation, you have convincing communication skills and negotiation security. - You have an independent, solution-oriented and structured approach. - If you are also a team player, reliable and very committed, then we should get to know each other. -  work-life balance With us you get flextime, 30 days vacation and more days off on Christmas Eve and New Year's Eve. You also have the opportunity for sabbaticals and temporary part-time work. -  Attractive employer benefits We also compensate any overtime work within the framework of the collective agreement of the AVH. In addition, you will receive a special annual payment and a 50% subsidy for the HVV Proficard.  -  Work-life balance You shape your everyday work – through mobile working and flexible working hours without core working hours.  - Corporate Health Management  With our company doctor and a health cost subsidy, we support you in promoting your health.  - Diversity and Equal Opportunities  We live diversity, tolerance and equal opportunities and offer you a working atmosphere with freedom for personal and professional development, short decision-making processes and flat hierarchies in a team characterized by mutual respect. -  More Benefits  Modern working environments in the heart of the city of Hamburg, bicycle leasing, bicycle parking spaces on site, company events, company pension scheme. Job Description: About Us  Junge Die Bäckerei has dedicated itself to “genuine enjoyment”. prescribed since 1897. The family business has been owner-managed for four generations and is much more than a bakery. The pillars of success include the 4,300 passionate employees as well as innovative spirit and high quality standards for baked goods, snacks and coffee specialties. Junge has received multiple awards for its products, employees and innovations, and is now one of the leading companies in the bakery and quick-service restaurant sectors. The company, with around 200 stores, has developed into a coveted brand throughout Northern Germany and Berlin.  Our sales staff appreciate the family atmosphere, the structured work and the security of a large, medium-sized company.  Trainee (m/f/d) Area Sales Manager - Berlin Would you like to contribute your skills to the commercial and personal support of our business? Would you like to take on responsibility, but you are still missing a few ingredients? As a trainee (m/f/d) for area sales management in the Berlin region, we offer you an intensive, structured training period for your subsequent job as area sales management. Join an expanding family business that offers you attractive benefits.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: sales pitch, business administration

Job Description: View job here  The senior citizens' facilities of the district of Würzburg gGmbH were founded in 1998. It employs over 500 people at eight locations. In addition to long-term and short-term care as well as day care, the holistic care of dementia sufferers and those in need of serious care is an important concern of the senior citizens' facilities. Nursing staff (m/f/d) for the living area "" Nursing""  * Full or part time * 97285 Roettingen, Germany * Without work experience * 02/20/23 In the senior center in Röttingen, a living area is being built according to the “care” concept. This concept is designed for the care, support and support of people between the ages of 18 and 65 who, due to a disability and/or neurological disease, are in need of care within the meaning of long-term care insurance and are therefore classified in a care level. The aim is to maintain the physical, mental and emotional independence of the residents for as long as possible.  We are therefore looking for nurses, nursing assistants and nursing assistants (m/f/d) for the senior center in Röttingen as soon as possible.  Your tasks * Support for or provision of basic care or basic and treatment care as well as care and support for the residents, depending on their qualifications * Recognizing and assessing the physical, mental, emotional and social needs as well as strengthening and promoting the skills of the residents * Planning, implementation and digital documentation of all care processes * Acquisition of care-related household activities * Interdisciplinary and constructive cooperation with all professional groups and relatives    your profile * Completed three-year vocational training as a geriatric nurse / nursing specialist or nursing specialist / health worker and nurse (m/f/d) or * Completed one-year vocational training as a nursing assistant (m/f/d) or comparable qualifications or * Nursing assistants with and without prior knowledge. We also welcome career changers. We offer * Crisis-proof employer * permanent employment * industry-standard remuneration according to collective agreement, depending on qualifications * 30 vacation days plus additional vacation for the care of children or relatives in need of care * Up to €100 childcare subsidy per month * Employee events (company bowling, eating asparagus, theme party, Christmas party) * Participation in the corporate benefits program * Car and e-bike leasing * Company subscription for local public transport * Company health management with subsidies for VHS courses for health promotion, working time credit for check-ups, and much more. Curious? Then we look forward to receiving your application!  If you have any questions about the “care” concept, please contact the care service manager, Mr Artur Hild, on 09338 9807-0.  If you have any questions about the application process, please do not hesitate to contact our nursing staff officer, Ms. Vanessa Drösler, on 0931 8009-1103. Senior citizens' facilities in the district of Würzburg Zeppelinstrasse 67 97074 Würzburg www.senioreneinrichtungen.info  Imprint | Data protection  Powered by softgarden

Job Description: They are an important part of our future. And hopefully we'll be a part of yours too! At B. Braun we protect and improve the health of people worldwide. This is also our vision in research and development. Because you see complexity as an opportunity and both quality and sustainability are important criteria in your work, we would like to work with you on the solutions of tomorrow. With trust, transparency and appreciation, we create sustainable healthcare together - locally, in regions, countries and worldwide. This is sharing expertise.  (Senior) Manager (m/f/d) Pharmaceutical Development Code number DEML429042-75849  For our Center of Excellence Vascular Systems of the B. Braun division Aesculap located in Berlin, we are looking for a (Senior) Manager (m/f/d) Pharmaceutical Development. tasks and responsibilities  * Management, coordination and implementation of development projects in the field of interventional cardiology and related fields * Development, application and adaptation of coating technologies for drug-coated medical devices for intravascular use * Development, prototyping and testing of drug-coated medical devices * Planning and creation of design specifications and product specifications * Coordination and evaluation of test series for design verification and product registration according to valid standards * Know-how transfer in development / production, particularly regarding coating processes, as part of the establishment of development products in routine production * Creation of MDR-compliant approval documentation (preparatory work for STED and eCTD) for product registration within and outside the CE area Technical skills  * Successfully completed studies in engineering or natural sciences (medical technology, mechanical engineering, pharmacy, chemistry, etc.) or comparable qualification * Several years of professional experience in the product development of medical devices, especially in the area of ​​combination products * Experience in the field of plant construction and process validation, especially in medical technology as well as knowledge of the relevant standards * Very good knowledge of spoken and written English * Confident use of MS Office applications * Intercultural competence and willingness to travel Personal skills * You appear ready to perform and take responsibility * You set high quality standards and act cost-consciously * Constructive interaction is a matter of course for you * You communicate clearly and responsibly our range  Take part in a corporate culture that actively promotes constructive exchange with colleagues, customers and partners. Work with us to improve people's lives in a sustainable way. We offer you a wide range of tasks and excellent development opportunities as well as attractive remuneration with extensive social benefits in a dynamic family business. benefits  * Flexible working hours * Attractive location in the federal capital Berlin * BVG job ticket * You can find more benefits on our website your next step  Enrich your career and apply via the global job market on our website (www.bbraun.de).

Job Description: You can now hire to strengthen our team as a  SPECIALIST (M/F/D) FOR GLOBAL SEA FREIGHT TRANSPORT As a specialist (m/f/d) for global sea freight transport, you are well networked and are available to advise and support our customers - from Ehingen or Bremerhaven, hybrid or remote. They negotiate with shipowners, prepare offers, organize freight space and connecting transports. Scheduling, order entry and on-carriage are done with ease. You will be part of a great team with a lot of know-how and have the best prospects for the future.  IMPORTANT FOR US * Professional experience in sea freight; Educational qualification an advantage * Good written and spoken English knowledge * Customer and service orientation * Reliability and friendliness * Responsibility and resilience * Confident use of MS Office programs  IMPORTANT FOR HER * Permanent employment * Interesting projects and a strong team * Varied field of activity * Very good working atmosphere * Punctual and performance-related payment * Training opportunities DENKINGER is a Swabian, family-run logistics company with around 250 employees. With passion, innovation and know-how we create competitive advantages for our business partners. We move goods of all kinds. And when it comes to IT, we create communication structures and platforms that we use to develop individually tailored solutions for each customer. Our goals are sustainable growth and long-term success. That spurs us and our employees on. With their commitment and their ideas, they contribute to our mutual success.  INTERESTED? Job Description: We are one of the leading medium-sized waste disposal and recycling companies in Baden-Württemberg with currently 6 locations. As a family-run company in Albstadt, we operate a state-of-the-art waste sorting and recycling plant and process alternative fuels. In this way, we actively contribute to environmental protection and significantly to the reduction of greenhouse gases.  Our containers shape the region, our employees the dynamics of our company. Become a part of us at one of our locations in Albstadt, Gammertingen or Riederich  Weighing supervisor / employee scales (m/f/d)

Job Description: MÜNZING CHEMIE GmbH has been a successful family business since 1830. Today we are represented as a hidden champion on four continents. More than 350 employees in Germany are responsible for the production of high-quality chemical additives. With our additives, we create added value for our wide range of customers from the coatings and paints industry, paper manufacturers and manufacturers of construction chemical products. To strengthen our team we are looking for you  Employee Product Safety Chemical Additives (m/f/x) at our Abstatt location.  The chemistry is right - in our international technology and administration center in Abstatt, you will work on product safety and regulatory issues across all locations.  your area of ​​responsibility * Creation and maintenance of safety data sheets and labels according to CLP/GHS * Maintenance of safety-relevant data of substances, raw materials and products in the existing IT landscape * Determination of the classification of our products and determination of the necessary labeling according to the current national and international chemical legislation * Comparison of the ingredients of our products with national registers of substances * Handling customer inquiries on chemical product safety * Communication with suppliers, customers and consultants  your profile * Successfully completed vocational training as a chemical-technical assistant, chemical laboratory assistant, chemical technician (f/m/d) or comparable qualification * First professional experience in the field of regulatory affairs * Strong analytical skills, quick comprehension and very careful way of working * Ability to work in a team, flexibility, initiative and good organizational skills * Safe handling of MS Office is assumed * Good knowledge of spoken and written German and English what we offer you * Industry standard pay and 30 days vacation * Long-term account * Flexitime model for the right balance between family and work * Fruit basket and free drinks, JobRad, charging stations for your electric car, financial and personal support for (part-time) further training and other benefits * Varied (project) tasks offer interesting development opportunities * Intensive, personal training by a mentor (m/f/d) * Working together on challenging projects with lively and open exchange in the team * Pleasant working atmosphere * Convenient motorway connection  We look forward to receiving your application!  Please send your comprehensive application, including information on your availability and your salary expectations, by email to bewerbung@munzing.com (max. 10 MB, permitted file formats .pdf, .docx, .jpg). Any questions?  Our personnel officer Andrea Wolpert will be happy to answer them on 07131 987-270. MÜNZING CHEMIE GmbH Münzingstrasse 2 74232 Abstatt Detailed information at www.munzing.com

Job Description: Cooperation Officer (m/f/d)  * Rostock * Presence / Mobile * Full time    The UKA Group has around 880 employees and is active in Europe, North and South America. As a full developer, UKA covers the entire value chain and also operates wind and solar parks itself. The company, founded in 1999, is one of the leading German project developers and currently has an onshore wind project pipeline of around 1.8 gigawatts in the approval process in Germany. UKA has also grown internationally in recent years. The current project pipeline of the UKA Group for wind and solar projects now includes more than 14 gigawatts. Your tasks  * Support for project development (wind, PV and grid) on cooperation topics * Coordination and organization of ongoing collaborations * Interdisciplinary coordination in the company * Networking and maintaining contact with external partners * Participation in the initiation, development and consolidation of business relationships * Coordination of project reviews and evaluations * Development of new strategic approaches * Further development of processes in the area of ​​project acquisition and cooperation  your profile * Completed studies at a university, technical college or vocational academy, e.g. public relations / communication management, environmental law, business administration (business administration) or comparable training * Strong communication and organizational skills * Enjoy interdisciplinary work with the willingness to familiarize yourself with new areas of responsibility * Quick comprehension, overarching thinking and a keen eye for the essentials * an independent way of working * Good to very good knowledge of MS Office applications * Basic knowledge of contract law is desirable, but not a requirement We offer you * a multifaceted area of ​​responsibility * A performance-related salary and 30 days vacation * Subject-specific further training opportunities tailored to your needs * Voluntary social benefits (company pension scheme, job ticket, company bicycle) * Opportunities for home office * modern office equipment, free drinks * regular team events * Very good connection to public transport Prior knowledge and professional experience in the field of developing projects for the use of renewable energies, especially wind energy, are desirable but not essential. A company is only as good as its employees. That's why we don't care about gender, skin color, religion or origin. In order to be able to help shape the future of renewable energies in the long term, what counts for us are commitment and competence. Let's work together to successfully implement the energy transition!  Apply now quickly and easily with just a few clicks.  * Hagen Bierstedt * CRE * +49 3521 72806-623 UKA Environmentally Friendly Kraftanlagen GmbH & Co. KG Dr.-Eberle-Platz 1 01662 Meissen Telephone 03521 728060 Fax 03521 72806410 central@uka-gruppe.de www.uka-gruppe.de

Job Description: With an annual program of around 5,000 events, the adult education center in Stuttgart is the largest in Baden-Württemberg and one of the largest adult education centers in Germany. As a public further education institution funded by the state capital of Stuttgart, it provides a wide range of educational opportunities related to the city and the educational needs of the citizens with close links to culture and social affairs. The courses, seminars, courses, individual events and series of events in the program areas of general and political education, cultural education, health education, languages ​​(especially German as a foreign language/integration), professional training and further education as well as basic education and school degrees are attended by more than 200,000 people every year . The participants can choose between face-to-face and online courses as well as hybrid formats. On behalf of the state capital Stuttgart, the vhs coordinates the cultural program in its central event building TREFFPUNKT Rotebühlplatz in the center of Stuttgart. In addition, the Volkshochschule stuttgart supports the largest night school in Baden-Württemberg with around 400 students per year. The offers of the children's meeting point and the vhs Ökostation as well as the large inclusive offer round off the spectrum.  For the subject of event coordination at TREFFPUNKT Rotebühlplatz we are looking for a person as soon as possible  Event Technology Team Leader (m/f/d)

Job Description: The German Children's Cancer Foundation is looking for a psychosocial manager (m/f/d) for your forest pirates camp in Heidelberg as soon as possible. Your tasks in this newly created managerial position include  * the conception and implementation of measures, seminars and qualifications within the framework of psychosocial aftercare for children with cancer, their parents and siblings, mainly at the Heidelberg location, but also nationwide and virtually * Close cooperation with the office of the German Children's Cancer Foundation in Bonn, e.g. in the preparation of publications and in the further development of offers and the assessment and support of psychosocial projects and research projects * Participation in the implementation of leisure camps — also during vacation periods and weekends We offer you * a permanent contract with 40 hours per week in a steadily growing organization * an interesting, meaningful job * Flexible working hours and a good work-life balance we expect from you * ideally training as a pediatric psycho-oncologist or psychologist, gladly with additional therapeutic training * Empathy, communication skills, resilience and the ability to work in a team * gladly experience in counseling and qualification of young people and adults as well as with crisis intervention and the topics of illness and death * Identification with our foundation purpose The German Children's Cancer Foundation promotes and finances clinical and patient-oriented research projects, supports affected families with competent advice and information as well as financial aid in emergencies and operates rehabilitation and leisure facilities on Sylt and in Heidelberg.

Job Description: Hire to make town. The Kiel Human Resources and Organization Office is looking for support  Hire as HR developer (remunerated according to EG 12 TVöD / A 12 SHBesG)  and become part of the Kiel city administration for an unlimited period of time full/part-time. The state capital Kiel is one of the largest employers and training companies in Schleswig-Holstein and currently employs more than 5,000 people in 27 offices, departments and companies. A family-friendly human resources policy in the form of part-time opportunities and mobile work, as well as a variety of jobs, an extensive training program and an additional pension scheme at the VBL are just a few of the advantages that the Kiel city administration offers. Kiel is a dynamic, cosmopolitan and rapidly growing city with more than 248,000 inhabitants and a high quality of life thanks to its unique location on the fjord.  What we offer - your advantages  • a diverse field of work that requires and desires active participation • a dynamic administration that trusts itself and its employees to change • the opportunity to combine family, free time and everyday work into a meaningful whole • varied sport and fitness offers • Flexible working hours in the context of changing processes and areas of responsibility • tailor-made commuter support - via job ticket or support for private bicycle procurement (including e-bikes) What to do - your new task • You are responsible for the conception and implementation as well as evaluation and, if necessary, adjustment of organizational and personnel development measures. • You advise employees and managers. • You introduce personnel development tools (e.g. knowledge management, e-learning, new work and advancement models) with the involvement of other offices and the responsible bodies. • You supervise and evaluate established programs of personnel development and develop them further. • You develop suitable information and communication concepts, coordinate them and implement them. • You select and commission external consultants, coaches and/or experts.  What you bring with you - your qualifications
Your contact for technical questions about the position is: Dr. Timo Rosenberg, Tel. 0431 901 1001.  Julia Holborn, Tel. 0431 901 5294, is responsible for the recruitment team.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Office communication MS Office
Advanced knowledge: personnel development

Job Description: Health is our greatest asset We – for life  BERLIN-CHEMIE AG belongs to the Italian Menarini Group and researches, produces and sells pharmaceutical products in more than 30 countries. Our commitment to health is what unites the many different employees in our company. With our responsible work, we ensure that patients can rely on us. Because we stand for life. USE YOUR POTENTIAL AS A Medical Assistant International (m/f/d) location Berlin subject area International career level young professionals time of entry from now on contract type temporary working hours full time home office Home office possible time of entry from now on contract type temporary working hours full time home office Home office possible  Your tasks You will support our medical team and the Drug Safety Coordinating Unit with daily tasks and general office organization. Due to your organizational talent, you ensure the timely processing of invoice management and the legalization of documents and take over the organization of business trips and appointments.  Another focus of your work is on conducting literature research and systematically archiving and distributing the resulting results. You support the provision of medical and scientific information materials and coordinate the updating and maintenance of documents for drug approval. In this context, you coordinate the translation of scientific documentation and support the creation of training materials and presentations. You bring your very good knowledge of English to bear in your day-to-day work and in communicating with our foreign organizations as needed. Job Description: The Ambulante Dienste e.V. association has been supporting people with disabilities and the elderly in maintaining their independence since 1982. Through advice, home care and personal assistance, it offers the opportunity to lead a life in familiar surroundings without paternalism. We are looking for a committed employee (m/f/d) with an hourly scope of 30 Whrs as soon as possible. (Deviation possible) for the "benefit accounting" in our administration at Bohlweg 10 in Münster. Ambulante Dienste e.V. currently employs around 250 full-time and part-time employees.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: billing, accounts receivable, customer data management

Personal requirements: Reliable and independent way of working Very good organizational and communication skills Strong entrepreneurial way of thinking and acting discretion and trustworthiness Confident demeanor and a strong service orientation The classification is between EG13 and EG15 depending on the fulfillment of the tasks. Handicapped applicants will be preferred with the same qualifications. Applicants who are from a Measures for job adjustments will be given preferential treatment.  Studies Comparable qualifications, at least a bachelor's degree or University degree in business administration with a focus on human resources Experience Human resources at least 3 years Several years of professional experience in operational HR work IT MS Office at least detailed. special skills SAP at least detailed special skills Workday - beneficial linguistic proficiency Business fluent German Business fluent English French - an advantage expertise Very good knowledge of the ERA North Württemberg/North Baden collective agreement other qualifications Current knowledge in works constitution law, labour, collective bargaining, wage tax and social security law Knowledge in the areas of moderation and organizational development

Job Description: The REGIOMED Medical Care Centers (MVZ) ensure that the people in our region receive outpatient medical care close to where they live, under municipal sponsorship. At a total of 15 locations in southern Thuringia and Upper Franconia, we treat our patients in various family and specialist disciplines. We see ourselves as a cooperation partner for resident doctors, outpatient aid and health services, and the clinics that provide further treatment. Our responsibility focuses on high-quality patient care and reliability as an employer for our employees.   We are looking for an outpatient oncology department at the REGIOMED MVZ Coburg as soon as possible Medical transcriptionist (m/f/d) for the outpatient oncology department  part-time (27.0 hours per week), limited as part of a parental leave replacement

Job Description: 
The tasks include answering the incoming calls at the head office and various central administrative services, e.g. e.g.: • the opening and distribution of the daily incoming mail • the processing of daily outgoing mail • checking tank receipts and entering them into an Excel file • Preparatory work for other departments • Monitoring of tenders • Keeping attendance lists • the forwarding of e-mails • the reception of visitors • stock control of office supplies • Applying for and managing certificates ... and other tasks that arise.  It is important to us that you appear friendly and courteous, both on the phone and when dealing with colleagues and customers. Good communication skills in German, both written and spoken, as well as confident handling of the common MS Office programs are prerequisites. Team spirit and flexibility complete the profile.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: telephone service
Advanced knowledge: Mail processing, office and administrative work, scheduling and monitoring

Job Description: Are you a goal-oriented team player? Do you not only master your field of work, but also want to act independently?  Our claim and goal is to solve problems for our clients and to find the most economically sensible solution. The trust of our clients forms the decisive basis for a successful cooperation. We, a medium-sized auditing and tax consulting company with four locations, specialize in restructuring and crisis consulting as well as advising insolvency administrators; who we support with tax issues in insolvency, the preparation and audit of annual financial statements, with going concern and restructuring.  To strengthen our team in Dresden, we are now looking for someone Assistant to the tax consultant (f/m/d) Gladly with professional experience in full or part time.  Your tasks  Preparation of annual financial statements, income surplus calculations and company tax returns  Support for professionals with tax advice, legal remedies and tax audits, etc.  your qualification  Successfully completed training as a tax clerk, tax specialist, accountant, Bachelor of Arts (WiWi), MBA or comparable  Application-ready knowledge in the areas of accounting and taxes  Service orientation and pleasure in client contact  Commitment and independent working methods  IT skills, especially DATEV and MS Excel Do you feel addressed?  Then become part of our team. In addition to a challenging, demanding and interesting job as well as individual training opportunities, you can expect flexible working hours, performance-related remuneration, social benefits and other company advantages, such as very good transport connections, free parking spaces and drinks.
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: business administration
Advanced knowledge: spreadsheet Excel (MS Office), annual financial statements, bookkeeping, bookkeeping, Datev program merchandise management, tax law

Job Description: Curatio Service & Building Management GmbH sees itself as an all-round service provider for social facilities. The company provides its services with 220 employees in currently 31 properties at 10 locations in Saxony-Anhalt. To strengthen our team, we are looking for a part-time kitchen helper (m/f/d) (30 hours/week) as soon as possible. The assignment takes place in our AWO Senior Center Zerbst - Haus Am Frauentor. Your duties will include assisting with the preparation of breakfast and dinner, e.g. B. Preparation of side dishes Support for all preparatory and follow-up work, e.g. B. Equipping the food trolley, arranging food and portioning dishes  Cleaning of dishes and kitchen appliances and operating the dishwashing line  Distribution of meals according to specifications Experience in the household sector Independent, reliable and organized way of working  Friendly and open manner in dealing with the residents  Service orientation  Teamwork and communication skills Opportunities for further training and development Provision and free cleaning of work clothes Individual training Regulated working hours, according to the roster with a 5-day week

The AWO-OPR non-profit social society mbH is the provider of numerous facilities and services for child and youth welfare as well as integration assistance. Our almost 200 full-time and 130 volunteer employees do great things every day. We are strong as a partner of people on their way to a successful life - with commitment, competence and passion. We stand for equal opportunities, self-determination and participation. Would you like to be part of the whole and get involved professionally? Then you are exactly right with us. For the holiday camp of our educational centers from 23.07.2023 to 06.08.2023 in Prerow we are looking for: Holiday camp supervisor (m/f/d). Your tasks are: The loving, warm and humorous accompaniment and care of our children aged 6 to 12 years in the above mentioned. Period Leisure and holiday activities by the sea in coordination with the male colleague, offering games and activities depending on the weather conditions Help for the younger children with everyday activities Educational training / educational studies or a youth leader card Reliability and joie de vivre Calmness and resilience A driver's license Class B A current first aid certificate Then we look forward to working with you! Job Description: Is it time for something new? Then think about switching to StegPlus GmbH. StegPlus GmbH is a ManpowerGroup company and the specialist in the healthcare sector. Manpower has been a successful personnel service provider in Germany since 1965 and, thanks to this experience and expertise, is one of the leading companies in the industry. We have already been able to help many specialists from the pharmaceutical industry to take new career steps. Be the next person we can offer good professional development to.  We are looking for a Project Management Support (gn) for a well-known pharmaceutical company in Mainz.

Job Description: Would you like more time to care for your clients, more relaxed work, personal and professional development or a job where you can say "That's why I became a nurse"?  —  ✔ That's what we offer you
• Sufficient time for the outpatient care of your client and for yourself through the model of 1: 1 care  • Stay technically fit. We offer a wide range of courses and further training opportunities, e.g. B. the non-clinical basic course • Ambulatory and home work environments where you can provide the help that is needed locally  •    As a nursing service that operates throughout Germany, you can be sure of your job with us even in times of crisis  • Permanent employment contract so that you can plan your life in the long term • Our heroes in care achieve a lot. When it comes to salary, you won't miss out with us  • With your Sunday and public holiday bonuses, an appropriate balance is ensured • Look forward to more money at the end of the month due to the night shift surcharge  • A better work-life balance is ensured with regulated duty times and uncomplicated co-creation of your duty rosters  • As a bipG nurse, you benefit from numerous discounts when shopping online via our employee portal, e.g. B. at CEWE PHOTOBOOK or Jochen Schweizer ✔ Your tasks  • Enable your client to lead an individual and self-determined life. You carry out basic, treatment and activation care independently and document care data ✔ Your profile  • You are a registered nurse, nurse, nurse (m/f/d) or geriatric nurse —
Become part of our bipG team as a part-time or full-time nurse for outpatient intensive care and 1: 1 care in Dorsten. Day shifts and night shifts are possible in 12-hour shifts. How do you apply? Quickly and easily by...  ✔ Email >> bewerbung(a)bipg.de ✔ Call >> 0511 12331410 ✔www.bipg.de/online-werbung/ Do you have any questions about us or the position? We are happy to answer your questions over the phone.  Your contact Aleksandr Cabanov  —
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: basic care, treatment care, care documentation
Advanced knowledge: patient care

Job Description: Have you just completed your training as a machine and plant operator or would you like to find a new career path? We will help you! On behalf of our customers, we are currently looking for reliable machine and plant operators in Limburg and the surrounding area. Your careful way of working and your good comprehension are your ticket to a varied job!
Our requirements: -Completed training as a machine and plant operator or a comparable qualification -Experience in the operation of machines and production facilities - Willingness to work shifts -High sense of quality and responsibility -Reliability, flexibility and ability to work in a team - Car and driver's license to reach the place of work is an advantage
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: maintenance, repair, servicing
Advanced knowledge: machine management, plant management, operation

Job Description: You search  • A great team and a supervisor who supports you • Attractive and fair remuneration • A future-proof job •    Flexible working hours • Short commutes to work • Tailored and appropriate training opportunities  We also welcome career changers (m/f/d), pensioners (m/f/d) or students (m/f/d) because who you are counts! you bring  • Independent and careful work • Punctual, reliable and helpful team player (m/f/d) • Service-oriented and hands-on personality • Open-minded in contact with residents (m/f/d) and customers (m/f/d)  Your tasks • Processing of residents' laundry • Assistance in the laundry  your working hours • Effective immediately, limited to 1 year - with the option of being taken on • Part-time, 20 hours/ week • Monday to Friday, 5 days/ week

Job Description: Ventilation engineer (m/f/d) industrial ventilation construction wanted in Kassel Lohfelden  That's what we offer you • Permanent full-time employment contract with above-average remuneration (from 17 euros per hour) • Holiday and Christmas bonuses • Long-term perspective with the option of being taken over by our customer • Support from our dedicated branch office team These are your tasks • Installation, commissioning, maintenance, servicing and repairs of ventilation and extraction systems • Recognizing and eliminating faults • Drawing and working according to plan • Supervision of technical tests Your skills  • You have completed training as a plant mechanic - sanitary, heating and air conditioning technology (m/f/x) or comparable • Willingness to assemble and travel • You have a driver's license and vehicle (desirable) • German language skills in speaking and writing  Interest? We look forward to receiving your application!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: Servicing, repairs, maintenance, pressure testing (pipeline, container construction), ventilation technology, machine management, system management and operation, customer service, electrical engineering, quality testing, quality assurance, building system technology, building control technology, ventilation systems

Job Description: Optikhaus Scheiper in Essen is looking for you Hearing aid acoustician in a managerial position (m/f/d)  We offer you - SAFE MONEY a permanent employment contract in a crisis-proof industry - HAPPY HOLIDAY at least 30 days holiday per year - WORK LIFE BALANCE On Wednesdays and Saturdays we only work until 1.30 p.m - TAKE CARE subsidy for company pension scheme and additional health insurance - GOOD VISION 2 free glasses per year and attractive family discounts - ONBOARDING Intensive induction and further training in our academy Your tasks - Expert needs analysis and advice to our customers - Fitting hearing aids - Audiometry - Carrying out repair and service work on hearing systems - Training of journeymen  your qualification - Completed examination as a hearing aid acoustician master - Enjoy interacting with people - Ability to inspire customers - Motivation for continuous training - Enjoy working in a team with different professional backgrounds
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: maintenance, repair, servicing
Advanced knowledge: hearing aid fitting, acoustics
Expert knowledge: Customer advice and support

Job Description: We are currently looking for CNC specialists for our business partners in the Limburg region. Your tasks  - Machining of workpieces - Carrying out measurements and tests - Programming, operation and monitoring of computer-controlled lathes - Execution of test runs - Maintenance and care of the machines  Our requirements - Completed training as a CNC specialist (m/f/d) or a comparable qualification - Work experience in a comparable position- Ideally knowledge of reading drawings - Manual dexterity desirable - Independent and careful way of working We look forward to receiving your application!
Requirements for Applicant: 
Advanced knowledge: CNC knowledge, CNC programming

Job Description: 
Company The BBHT consulting company is a management consultancy that supports customers from strategic advice to professional, technical implementation. Our focus is on the implementation of IT projects. We specialize in the banking and insurance, telecommunications and healthcare sectors. BBHT consultants are experienced business analysts and project managers who are technically and professionally highly qualified, socially competent and good at communicating. We are looking for you as a management consultant (m/f/d) in Münster, Frankfurt or remote Münster Full-time tasks Independent advice, management and implementation of our customers' banking and insurance projects Recording, analysis and conception of requirements, coordination with the project team and Stakeholders Active support in the implementation of legal & regulatory requirements Cooperation in partnership & open communication with our customers Requirements In-depth & several years of experience in the banking or insurance industry Extensive methodical & conceptual experience & skills in project management or in business analysis Independent & communicative personality with IT affinity and willingness to travel We offer a good work-life balance through flexible working hours, paid overtime & 30 days of holiday office days, home office, MacBook, iPhone, company car or bicycle, 1st class rail card if required, free snacks & drinks in the office Qualified regular further training, participation in IT conferences & company events A permanent position in a highly motivated team Independent work, challenging & innovative projects with well-known customers Have we aroused your interest? We offer you a unique opportunity to get involved in an innovative environment and to develop yourself further. Our team looks forward to getting to know you and benefiting from your know-how and enthusiasm. We are looking forward to your application! APPLY HERE Contact person: Enrico Funnekötter BBHTberatungsgesellschaft mbH & Co. KG Am Mittelhafen 14 • 48155 Münster

Job Description: WHY YOU SHOULD START AT GERMAN HYGIENE LIQUIDS German Hygiene Liquids GmbH is a modern industrial company for the effective and efficient production of hygiene and cleaning agents. Based on more than 100 years of experience in the Genthin chemical park between Magdeburg and Berlin, German Hygiene Liquids manufactures the products for professional use and marketing on an area of ​​30,000 square meters on behalf of customers. - Diverse tasks and a working environment in which you can make a difference - Independent work and a collegial cooperation - qualified training  WHAT DOES A FORKLIFT DRIVER (M/F/D) AT GERMAN HYGIENE LIQUIDS - You are responsible for the clearing away of production results - You transport production parts to the plant for further processing - Your work supports the production process - Regular documentation gives you the opportunity to organize your work efficiently - Support of the team WHAT YOU SHOULD BRING WITH YOU - You have a forklift license - You have sufficient professional experience in driving industrial trucks (reach trucks). - First professional experience in the chemical industry desirable - Very good knowledge of spoken and written German - careful, structured and reliable way of working - Dedicated team player attitude with a high degree of independence, flexibility and resilience
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: warehouse work
Advanced knowledge: operate forklifts (diesel, petrol, electric, gas), conveyor systems and transport equipment, loading, unloading

Job Description: The municipality of Eching, Landshut district, approx. 4,200 inhabitants, is looking for a / n  Employee (m/f/d) for financial administration part-time (at least 30 hours) or full-time
Your main tasks include: - Processing property, trade and dog tax - Rental and leasing - Fee accounting for parish lunchtime care and playgroups - Insurance - Arrangements, e-invoice - Participation in the finance department
Requirements for Applicant: 
Basic knowledge: clerical work
